      "instruction": "Turn on oven to 200 Celsius."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Cook pasta in heavily salted water according to instructions on pack but reduce cooking time by 3 mins. When the pasta is 3 min from being ready, add all the broccoli. Cook for 3 further mins and then drain, reserving the pasta water (KEY)."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "In the meantime, heat the oil over high heat, add the chicken and cook for about 5 mins (not fully cooked), add salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Add the ricotta, pesto to a beaker and add about 200ml drained pasta water and mix."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Combine the pasta, broccoli, chicken, cherry tomatoes and ricotta-pesto sauce to a large oven tray, and mix. Cover with as much salt and pepper as desired and place in the oven for 15-20 mins until the top is crispy and the chicken is cooked through."
    },
    {
      "ingredient_lines": [],
      "instruction": "Keeps well in the fridge for 3 days!"
